 Alice — Personal AI Assistant (JARVIS-inspired)                                                                                                                
                                                        
 Context

 Chester wants to build "Alice" — a personal AI assistant that lives entirely on his PC, inspired by Iron Man's JARVIS. Female AI, bilingual (EN/JA),
 voice-loyal to creator only, controls the PC (apps, files, games), learns from interactions. Two activation modes: double clap (full Iron Man boot sequence
 with music + weather + news) and "Hey Alice" (quiet start). Both voice and chat input, always voice + chat log output.

 Hardware:

 ┌─────┬──────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐
 │     │       Desktop        │ Laptop (primary dev) │
 ├─────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
 │ CPU │ Ryzen 5 4600G 6C/12T │ Ryzen 7 5700U 8C/16T │
 ├─────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
 │ RAM │ 32 GB                │ 8 GB                 │
 ├─────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
 │ GPU │ RTX 3050 8GB         │ Radeon integrated    │
 └─────┴──────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘

 Constraint: 8GB laptop → cloud LLM mandatory. Desktop RTX 3050 → can run small local models via Ollama.

 Reusable code found:
 - D:/DEV/CHESTER/my_ai/ — FastAPI + Ollama + SQLite + SSE streaming (Chester's existing AI project)
 - D:/DEV/github/friday-tony-stark-demo/ — Python voice assistant with pluggable STT/LLM/TTS providers
 - D:/DEV/github/CLAUDE_LEAKED_SOURCECODE/ — Tool system patterns, memory system, command registry

